{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1117,"text":"How many people here would like to live\nto be at least 80 years old?"},{"time":6072,"text":"Yeah."},{"time":7571,"text":"I think we all have\nthis hopeful expectation"},{"time":10390,"text":"of living into old age."},{"time":12828,"text":"Let's project out into the future,"},{"time":14938,"text":"to your future \"you's,\""},{"time":16522,"text":"and let's imagine that we're all 85."},{"time":19894,"text":"Now, everyone look at two people."},{"time":23151,"text":"One of you probably has\nAlzheimer's disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27365,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":30813,"text":"Alright, alright."},{"time":32954,"text":"And maybe you're thinking,\n\"Well, it won't be me.\""},{"time":37350,"text":"Then, OK. You are a caregiver."},{"time":41388,"text":"So --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":42576,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":45472,"text":"so in some way,"},{"time":46853,"text":"this terrifying disease\nis likely to affect us all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50933,"text":"Part of the fear around Alzheimer's\nstems from the sense"},{"time":53971,"text":"that there's nothing we can do about it."},{"time":56409,"text":"Despite decades of research, we still\nhave no disease-modifying treatment"},{"time":61558,"text":"and no cure."},{"time":63321,"text":"So if we're lucky enough\nto live long enough,"},{"time":65814,"text":"Alzheimer's appears to be\nour brain's destiny."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69369,"text":"But maybe it doesn't have to be."},{"time":71585,"text":"What if I told you we could\nchange these statistics,"},{"time":74974,"text":"literally change our brain's destiny,"},{"time":77688,"text":"without relying on a cure\nor advancements in medicine?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":81983,"text":"Let's begin by looking at\nwhat we currently understand"},{"time":84532,"text":"about the neuroscience of Alzheimer's."},{"time":87730,"text":"Here's a picture\nof two neurons connecting."},{"time":90763,"text":"The point of connection,\nthis space circled in red,"},{"time":94144,"text":"is called the synapse."},{"time":95807,"text":"The synapse is where\nneurotransmitters are released."},{"time":99023,"text":"This is where signals are transmitted,\nwhere communication happens."},{"time":103315,"text":"This is where we think,\nfeel, see, hear, desire ..."},{"time":108445,"text":"and remember."},{"time":110118,"text":"And the synapse\nis where Alzheimer's happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113040,"text":"Let's zoom in on the synapse"},{"time":115026,"text":"and look at a cartoon representation\nof what's going on."},{"time":118799,"text":"During the business\nof communicating information,"},{"time":121110,"text":"in addition to releasing neurotransmitters\nlike glutamate into the synapse,"},{"time":125132,"text":"neurons also release a small peptide\ncalled amyloid beta."},{"time":130617,"text":"Normally, amyloid beta is cleared away\nmetabolized by microglia,"},{"time":135625,"text":"the janitor cells of our brains."},{"time":138405,"text":"While the molecular causes\nof Alzheimer's are still debated,"},{"time":142288,"text":"most neuroscientists believe\nthat the disease begins"},{"time":145566,"text":"when amyloid beta begins to accumulate."},{"time":148967,"text":"Too much is released,\nor not enough is cleared away,"},{"time":151740,"text":"and the synapse begins\nto pile up with amyloid beta."},{"time":155098,"text":"And when this happens, it binds to itself,"},{"time":157341,"text":"forming sticky aggregates\ncalled amyloid plaques."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161582,"text":"How many people here\nare 40 years old or older?"},{"time":165184,"text":"You're afraid to admit it now."},{"time":167728,"text":"This initial step into the disease,"},{"time":169978,"text":"this presence of amyloid\nplaques accumulating,"},{"time":173086,"text":"can already be found in your brains."},{"time":176271,"text":"The only way we could be sure of this\nwould be through a PET scan,"},{"time":179765,"text":"because at this point,\nyou are blissfully unaware."},{"time":183605,"text":"You're not showing any impairments\nin memory, language, or cognition ..."},{"time":187918,"text":"yet."},{"time":189471,"text":"We think it takes at least 15 to 20 years\nof amyloid plaque accumulation"},{"time":194032,"text":"before it reaches a tipping point,"},{"time":196437,"text":"then triggering a molecular cascade"},{"time":198696,"text":"that causes the clinical\nsymptoms of the disease."},{"time":201810,"text":"Prior to the tipping point,"},{"time":203795,"text":"your lapses in memory\nmight include things like,"},{"time":207403,"text":"\"Why did I come in this room?\""},{"time":209752,"text":"or \"Oh ... what's his name?\""},{"time":212479,"text":"or \"Where did I put my keys?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":215553,"text":"Now, before you all\nstart freaking out again,"},{"time":218133,"text":"because I know half of you did at least\none of those in the last 24 hours --"},{"time":223555,"text":"these are all normal kinds of forgetting."},{"time":226816,"text":"In fact, I would argue that these examples"},{"time":229153,"text":"might not even involve your memory,"},{"time":231154,"text":"because you didn't pay attention\nto where you put your keys"},{"time":234070,"text":"in the first place."},{"time":235439,"text":"After the tipping point,"},{"time":237141,"text":"the glitches in memory,\nlanguage and cognition are different."},{"time":240688,"text":"Instead of eventually finding\nyour keys in your coat pocket"},{"time":243612,"text":"or on the table by the door,"},{"time":245638,"text":"you find them in the refrigerator,"},{"time":248376,"text":"or you find them and you think,"},{"time":250366,"text":"\"What are these for?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":252843,"text":"So what happens when amyloid plaques\naccumulate to this tipping point?"},{"time":258075,"text":"Our microglia janitor cells\nbecome hyper-activated,"},{"time":261418,"text":"releasing chemicals that cause\ninflammation and cellular damage."},{"time":265576,"text":"We think they might actually\nstart clearing away"},{"time":268195,"text":"the synapses themselves."},{"time":270398,"text":"A crucial neural transport protein\ncalled \"tau\" becomes hyperphosphorylated"},{"time":274870,"text":"and twists itself\ninto something called \"tangles,\""},{"time":277478,"text":"which choke off the neurons\nfrom the inside."},{"time":280537,"text":"By mid-stage Alzheimer's,\nwe have massive inflammation and tangles"},{"time":284395,"text":"and all-out war at the synapse"},{"time":286366,"text":"and cell death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288238,"text":"So if you were a scientist\ntrying to cure this disease,"},{"time":291350,"text":"at what point would you ideally\nwant to intervene?"},{"time":295134,"text":"Many scientists are betting big\non the simplest solution:"},{"time":299062,"text":"keep amyloid plaques\nfrom reaching that tipping point,"},{"time":302920,"text":"which means that drug discovery is largely\nfocused on developing a compound"},{"time":306972,"text":"that will prevent, eliminate, or reduce\namyloid plaque accumulation."},{"time":312859,"text":"So the cure for Alzheimer's will likely be\na preventative medicine."},{"time":318072,"text":"We're going to have to take this pill\nbefore we reach that tipping point,"},{"time":321525,"text":"before the cascade is triggered,"},{"time":323801,"text":"before we start leaving\nour keys in the refrigerator."},{"time":327381,"text":"We think this is why, to date,\nthese kinds of drugs have failed"},{"time":331078,"text":"in clinical trials --"},{"time":332339,"text":"not because the science wasn't sound,"},{"time":334808,"text":"but because the people in these trials\nwere already symptomatic."},{"time":338966,"text":"It was too late."},{"time":340722,"text":"Think of amyloid plaques as a lit match."},{"time":343998,"text":"At the tipping point, the match\nsets fire to the forest."},{"time":347884,"text":"Once the forest is ablaze,"},{"time":349858,"text":"it doesn't do any good\nto blow out the match."},{"time":352364,"text":"You have to blow out the match\nbefore the forest catches fire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356331,"text":"Even before scientists sort this out,"},{"time":358218,"text":"this information is actually\nreally good news for us,"},{"time":361110,"text":"because it turns out that the way we live\ncan influence the accumulation"},{"time":365178,"text":"of amyloid plaques."},{"time":366431,"text":"And so there are things we can do"},{"time":368031,"text":"to keep us from reaching\nthat tipping point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371117,"text":"Let's picture your risk\nof Alzheimer's as a see-saw scale."},{"time":375029,"text":"We're going to pile\nrisk factors on one arm,"},{"time":377102,"text":"and when that arm hits the floor,\nyou are symptomatic"},{"time":379604,"text":"and diagnosed with Alzheimer's."},{"time":382058,"text":"Let's imagine you're 50 years old."},{"time":384801,"text":"You're not a spring chicken anymore,"},{"time":386560,"text":"so you've accumulated\nsome amyloid plaques with age."},{"time":389656,"text":"Your scale is tipped a little bit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392323,"text":"Now let's look at your DNA."},{"time":394536,"text":"We've all inherited our genes\nfrom our moms and our dads."},{"time":398112,"text":"Some of these genes will increase our risk\nand some will decrease it."},{"time":402214,"text":"If you're like Alice in \"Still Alice,\""},{"time":404427,"text":"you've inherited a rare genetic mutation\nthat cranks out amyloid beta,"},{"time":409002,"text":"and this alone will tip\nyour scale arm to the ground."},{"time":412579,"text":"But for most of us, the genes we inherit\nwill only tip the arm a bit."},{"time":416769,"text":"For example, APOE4 is a gene variant\nthat increases amyloid,"},{"time":421608,"text":"but you can inherit a copy of APOE4\nfrom mom and dad"},{"time":424900,"text":"and still never get Alzheimer's,"},{"time":427315,"text":"which means that for most of us,"},{"time":429452,"text":"our DNA alone does not determine\nwhether we get Alzheimer's."},{"time":433984,"text":"So what does?"},{"time":435482,"text":"We can't do anything about getting older\nor the genes we've inherited."},{"time":439298,"text":"So far, we haven't changed\nour brain's destiny."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443144,"text":"What about sleep?"},{"time":445278,"text":"In slow-wave deep sleep, our glial cells\nrinse cerebral spinal fluid"},{"time":449384,"text":"throughout our brains,"},{"time":450624,"text":"clearing away metabolic waste\nthat accumulated in our synapses"},{"time":454220,"text":"while we were awake."},{"time":456145,"text":"Deep sleep is like\na power cleanse for the brain."},{"time":459646,"text":"But what happens if you shortchange\nyourself on sleep?"},{"time":463421,"text":"Many scientists believe"},{"time":464977,"text":"that poor sleep hygiene might actually\nbe a predictor of Alzheimer's."},{"time":469613,"text":"A single night of sleep deprivation\nleads to an increase in amyloid beta."},{"time":475410,"text":"And amyloid accumulation\nhas been shown to disrupt sleep,"},{"time":478860,"text":"which in turn causes\nmore amyloid to accumulate."},{"time":481371,"text":"And so now we have\nthis positive feedback loop"},{"time":483871,"text":"that's going to accelerate\nthe tipping of that scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487306,"text":"What else?"},{"time":488753,"text":"Cardiovascular health."},{"time":491043,"text":"High blood pressure, diabetes,\nobesity, smoking, high cholesterol,"},{"time":494812,"text":"have all been shown to increase our risk\nof developing Alzheimer's."},{"time":498972,"text":"Some autopsy studies have shown"},{"time":500887,"text":"that as many as 80 percent\nof people with Alzheimer's"},{"time":503583,"text":"also had cardiovascular disease."},{"time":506369,"text":"Aerobic exercise has been shown\nin many studies to decrease amyloid beta"},{"time":511398,"text":"in animal models of the disease."},{"time":513619,"text":"So a heart-healthy\nMediterranean lifestyle and diet"},{"time":517223,"text":"can help to counter\nthe tipping of this scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520697,"text":"So there are many things we can do"},{"time":523070,"text":"to prevent or delay\nthe onset of Alzheimer's."},{"time":525466,"text":"But let's say\nyou haven't done any of them."},{"time":528211,"text":"Let's say you're 65;"},{"time":530689,"text":"there's Alzheimer's in your family,\nso you've likely inherited a gene or two"},{"time":534379,"text":"that tips your scale arm a bit;"},{"time":536427,"text":"you've been burning the candle\nat both ends for years;"},{"time":539183,"text":"you love bacon;"},{"time":540710,"text":"and you don't run unless\nsomeone's chasing you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542957,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":544282,"text":"Let's imagine that your amyloid plaques\nhave reached that tipping point."},{"time":547918,"text":"Your scale arm has crashed to the floor."},{"time":549990,"text":"You've tripped the cascade,"},{"time":551695,"text":"setting fire to the forest,"},{"time":553285,"text":"causing inflammation, tangles,\nand cell death."},{"time":557137,"text":"You should be symptomatic for Alzheimer's."},{"time":559820,"text":"You should be having trouble\nfinding words and keys"},{"time":563160,"text":"and remembering what I said\nat the beginning of this talk."},{"time":566917,"text":"But you might not be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569180,"text":"There's one more thing you can do\nto protect yourself"},{"time":571682,"text":"from experiencing\nthe symptoms of Alzheimer's,"},{"time":574292,"text":"even if you have the full-blown disease\npathology ablaze in your brain."},{"time":578807,"text":"It has to do with neural plasticity\nand cognitive reserve."},{"time":583261,"text":"Remember, the experience\nof having Alzheimer's"},{"time":585662,"text":"is ultimately a result of losing synapses."},{"time":589339,"text":"The average brain has\nover a hundred trillion synapses,"},{"time":592740,"text":"which is fantastic;\nwe've got a lot to work with."},{"time":595477,"text":"And this isn't a static number."},{"time":597170,"text":"We gain and lose synapses all the time,"},{"time":599592,"text":"through a process\ncalled neural plasticity."},{"time":602419,"text":"Every time we learn something new,"},{"time":604515,"text":"we are creating and strengthening\nnew neural connections,"},{"time":608666,"text":"new synapses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610988,"text":"In the Nun Study,"},{"time":612587,"text":"678 nuns, all over the age of 75\nwhen the study began,"},{"time":617504,"text":"were followed for more than two decades."},{"time":619837,"text":"They were regularly given\nphysical checkups and cognitive tests,"},{"time":623321,"text":"and when they died, their brains\nwere all donated for autopsy."},{"time":627393,"text":"In some of these brains, scientists\ndiscovered something surprising."},{"time":631792,"text":"Despite the presence of plaques\nand tangles and brain shrinkage --"},{"time":636392,"text":"what appeared to be\nunquestionable Alzheimer's --"},{"time":639285,"text":"the nuns who had belonged\nto these brains showed no signs"},{"time":642988,"text":"of having the disease\nwhile they were alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646181,"text":"How can this be?"},{"time":648009,"text":"We think it's because these nuns\nhad a high level of cognitive reserve,"},{"time":652160,"text":"which is a way of saying that they had\nmore functional synapses."},{"time":656107,"text":"People who have more years\nof formal education,"},{"time":658705,"text":"who have a high degree of literacy,"},{"time":660964,"text":"who engage regularly\nin mentally stimulating activities,"},{"time":664567,"text":"all have more cognitive reserve."},{"time":667072,"text":"They have an abundance\nand a redundancy in neural connections."},{"time":671223,"text":"So even if they have a disease\nlike Alzheimer's"},{"time":673927,"text":"compromising some of their synapses,"},{"time":676005,"text":"they've got many extra backup connections,"},{"time":679014,"text":"and this buffers them from noticing\nthat anything is amiss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682977,"text":"Let's imagine a simplified example."},{"time":685263,"text":"Let's say you only know one thing\nabout a subject."},{"time":688013,"text":"Let's say it's about me."},{"time":689566,"text":"You know that Lisa Genova\nwrote \"Still Alice,\""},{"time":691896,"text":"and that's the only thing\nyou know about me."},{"time":694356,"text":"You have that single neural connection,"},{"time":696770,"text":"that one synapse."},{"time":698740,"text":"Now imagine you have Alzheimer's."},{"time":700925,"text":"You have plaques and tangles\nand inflammation"},{"time":703282,"text":"and microglia devouring that synapse."},{"time":706603,"text":"Now when someone asks you,\n\"Hey, who wrote 'Still Alice?'\""},{"time":710857,"text":"you can't remember,"},{"time":712126,"text":"because that synapse\nis either failing or gone."},{"time":715333,"text":"You've forgotten me forever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717760,"text":"But what if you had learned more about me?"},{"time":720410,"text":"Let's say you learned\nfour things about me."},{"time":722523,"text":"Now imagine you have Alzheimer's,"},{"time":724392,"text":"and three of those synapses\nare damaged or destroyed."},{"time":728077,"text":"You still have a way\nto detour the wreckage."},{"time":730562,"text":"You can still remember my name."},{"time":733283,"text":"So we can be resilient\nto the presence of Alzheimer's pathology"},{"time":737233,"text":"through the recruitment\nof yet-undamaged pathways."},{"time":740360,"text":"And we create these pathways,\nthis cognitive reserve,"},{"time":744163,"text":"by learning new things."},{"time":746455,"text":"Ideally, we want these new things\nto be as rich in meaning as possible,"},{"time":751000,"text":"recruiting sight and sound\nand associations and emotion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756398,"text":"So this really doesn't mean\ndoing crossword puzzles."},{"time":759557,"text":"You don't want to simply retrieve\ninformation you've already learned,"},{"time":763678,"text":"because this is like traveling\ndown old, familiar streets,"},{"time":767045,"text":"cruising neighborhoods you already know."},{"time":770113,"text":"You want to pave new neural roads."},{"time":772971,"text":"Building an Alzheimer's-resistant brain"},{"time":775507,"text":"means learning to speak Italian,"},{"time":777711,"text":"meeting new friends,"},{"time":779245,"text":"reading a book,"},{"time":780436,"text":"or listening to a great TED Talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783283,"text":"And if, despite all of this, you are\nsomeday diagnosed with Alzheimer's,"},{"time":788620,"text":"there are three lessons I've learned\nfrom my grandmother"},{"time":791797,"text":"and the dozens of people I've come to know\nliving with this disease."},{"time":796115,"text":"Diagnosis doesn't mean\nyou're dying tomorrow."},{"time":799323,"text":"Keep living."},{"time":801069,"text":"You won't lose your emotional memory."},{"time":803459,"text":"You'll still be able\nto understand love and joy."},{"time":806989,"text":"You might not remember\nwhat I said five minutes ago,"},{"time":810016,"text":"but you'll remember how I made you feel."},{"time":812944,"text":"And you are more than what\nyou can remember."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816244,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817557,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}